00:43:21.380 --> 00:43:25.190
this is how my mother
used to test us.

00:43:25.190 --> 00:43:27.080
She would say, go get an orange.

00:43:27.080 --> 00:43:29.870
And we'd bring in an orange.

00:43:29.870 --> 00:43:31.790
And she would cut
out all the pieces,

00:43:31.790 --> 00:43:33.470
and share with everybody.

00:43:33.470 --> 00:43:37.580
And if you were
new at our house,

00:43:37.580 --> 00:43:40.850
my mother would know if
you were a sharer or not.

00:43:40.850 --> 00:43:43.750
If you didn't know how
to share, my mother then

00:43:43.750 --> 00:43:46.340
would literally invite
you to the family,

00:43:46.340 --> 00:43:48.220
and you would
learn how to share.

00:43:48.220 --> 00:43:51.260
And you're going to live
learning how to share.

00:43:51.260 --> 00:43:54.620
But it was her secret.

00:43:54.620 --> 00:43:57.810
I find myself sometimes doing
that to people, especially

00:43:57.810 --> 00:43:58.310
with food.

00:43:58.310 --> 00:43:59.560
And some people don't like it.

00:44:05.720 --> 00:44:08.740
I think back to
this often in trying

00:44:08.740 --> 00:44:13.210
to make sense of the world;
how there are people who

00:44:13.210 --> 00:44:17.110
have so much and people
who have so little,

00:44:17.110 --> 00:44:22.220
and how I fit in with them both.

00:44:22.220 --> 00:44:27.470
Often I find myself trying to
bridge the two worlds to show

00:44:27.470 --> 00:44:30.950
people either the
people who have so much

00:44:30.950 --> 00:44:36.600
or the people with so little
that everything's yours,

00:44:36.600 --> 00:44:40.160
and everything is not yours.

00:44:40.160 --> 00:44:45.620
I wish to invite
you to understand

00:44:45.620 --> 00:44:52.470
that boxing ourselves into tiny
cubbies based on class, race,

00:44:52.470 --> 00:44:57.470
ethnicity, religion,
anything really,

00:44:57.470 --> 00:45:03.550
comes from a poverty of mind,
a poverty of imagination.

00:45:03.550 --> 00:45:08.110
The world is dull and cruel
when we isolate ourselves.

00:45:12.100 --> 00:45:17.120
Survival, the true survival
of the body and the soul,

00:45:17.120 --> 00:45:22.550
and now I've added on in spirit,
requires creativity, freedom

00:45:22.550 --> 00:45:26.270
of thoughts, and collaboration.

00:45:26.270 --> 00:45:29.810
You might have time,
and I might have land.

00:45:29.810 --> 00:45:33.650
You might have an idea,
and I might have strength.

00:45:33.650 --> 00:45:38.270
You might have a tomato,
and I might have a knife.

00:45:38.270 --> 00:45:40.940
We need each other.

00:45:40.940 --> 00:45:47.390
We need to say, I honor the
things that you respect,

00:45:47.390 --> 00:45:50.305
and I value the things
that you cherish.

00:45:53.360 --> 00:45:55.690
I am not better than you.

00:45:55.690 --> 00:45:57.760
You are not better than me.

00:45:57.760 --> 00:46:02.470
Nobody is better
than anybody else.

00:46:02.470 --> 00:46:07.400
Nobody is who you think
they are at first glance.

00:46:07.400 --> 00:46:12.490
We need to see beyond the
projection, the categories we

00:46:12.490 --> 00:46:16.120
cast into each other.

00:46:16.120 --> 00:46:25.920
Each one of us is so grand,
more nuanced, more extraordinary

00:46:25.920 --> 00:46:29.490
than anybody thinks,
including ourselves.

